# Specs entry (`specs/PROJECT.md`)

On **session start** or before **non-trivial** code/spec work, read **`<workspace>/specs/PROJECT.md`** when it exists. There is **no** alternate filename — do not look for `project.living.md` or other aliases.

If `specs/PROJECT.md` is missing, treat the repo as **specs-light**: use optional `.cursorrules` (for **Technologies** if present) + `011-orchestrator-reference.mdc`.

## What `PROJECT.md` should contain (convention)

| Section | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **Intent** / **Technologies** | Short lines at the top — drive **domain** detection with `011-orchestrator-reference.mdc` (no `.cursorrules` required). |
| **AI routing** (recommended) | Where domain/workflows are defined globally; table of **next files** (ADRs, cross-cutting, features) — not a duplicate of `011`. |
| **Feature / cross-cutting / ADR indexes** | Pointers or embedded tables so agents know which `specs/**` files exist. |
| **Optional: org hints** | e.g. ClickUp for features, `knowledge-audit` for SDD closure — short bullets. |

Keep **workflow YAML paths** and **domain matrices** in global rules (`011-orchestrator-reference.mdc`), not in `PROJECT.md`, unless the repo overrides with rare monorepo tables in optional `.cursorrules`.

## Orchestrator

`010-orchestrator.mdc` Step 0 preflight references this rule for the **Specs** bullet.
